EXTRACTED VALUE: The graphics are top-notch and the sound helps immerse you in the wonderfully rendered action.
Never have I seen a concept so perfectly implemented that a relatively tiny patch of land has me utterly captivated. [Jan. 2007, p.60]
As you play the game you just can’t help dropping your jaw in amazement at what you’re seeing and getting to do.
Just skip the plot (filled with hyper-cool words like "rendezvous" and "amnesia") and you'll be stranded in bug-blasting, giant robot heaven.
Battlefield: Bad Company is one of the most entertaining shooters ever released.
